OL,6,FThe number of sites rated "poor" has
OL,7,Fjumped to the highest level since the
OL,8,Fcurrent classification system began in
OL,9,F2015.
OL,11,FHowever, officials from the
OL,12,FEnvironment Agency said this was in
OL,13,Fpart due to the designation of new
OL,14,Fareas which weren't previously managed
OL,15,Fto meet bathing water standards.
OL,17,FMany of these new sites failing to
OL,18,Fmake the grade are river waters, which
OL,19,Fcampaigners say highlights how much
OL,20,Fpollution is being pumped into rivers
OL,21,Fand estuaries.
